similarity) md_positions.append((position, md_idx)) md_positions.sort(key=lambda x: x[0]) ordered_cells = [(i, cell["id"]) for i, cell in enumerate(code_cells)] ordered_cells += [ (pos, markdown_cells[md_idx]["id"]) for pos, md_idx in md_positions ] ordered_cells.sort(key=lambda x: x[0]) return [cell_id for _, cell_id in ordered_cells] # Validation val_scores = [] for idx, notebook_id in enumerate(val_ids[:1000]): if idx % 100 == 0: print(f"Processing validation notebook {idx}") json_path = f"./input/train/{notebook_id}.json" code_cells, markdown_cells = process_notebook(json_path) predicted_order = predict_cell_order(code_cells, markdown_cells) true_order = train_orders[train_orders["id"] == notebook_id]["cell_order"].iloc[0] if len(predicted_order) != len(true_order): tau = -1 else: true_ranks = {cell_id: i for i, cell_id in enumerate(true_order)} predicted_ranks = [true_ranks[cell_id] for cell_id in predicted_order] tau, _ = kendalltau(predicted_ranks, list(range(len(predicted_ranks)))) val_scores.append(tau) print(f"Validation Kendall Tau: {np.nanmean(val_scores)}") # Generate submission test_dir = "./input/test/" submission = [] for fname in os.listdir(test_dir): if not fname.endswith(".json"): continue notebook_id = fname[:-5] json_path = os.path.join(test_dir, fname) code_cells, markdown_cells = process_notebook(json_path) predicted_order = predict_cell_order(code_cells, markdown_cells) submission.append({"id": notebook_id, "cell_order": " ".join(predicted_order)}) pd.DataFrame(submission).to_csv("./submission/submission.csv", index=False) print("Submission file created successfully.")
